<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-656-871  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 656 871.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Nov 26 1990 v12 n48 p49(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FDDI standard to further complicate LAN communications. (FiberDistributed Data Interface, local area network) (Tech Street)(column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gantz, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Fiber Distributed Data Interface (FDDI) ANSI standard for100Mbps local area networks is nearing completion and adoption.andO;IBM and DEC reportedly already have customers clamoring for100Mbps to connect LANs and 100Mbps communications at the desktop.andO;The standard has been in development for six years.andP;  The 1990 FDDImarket reached $34 million, the 1995 market is estimated at $1billion.andP;  Concerns center on using FDDI as a backbone LAN forseveral buildings or building-wide, interdepartmental LANs, andbandwidth demand for departmental LANs.andP;  Other questions includehow the cabling should be run and how a FDDI LAN should besegmented for maximum reliability.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Fiber Distributed Data Interface StandardStandardsLocal Area NetworksInterfaceMarket Analysis.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>